<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7089&amp;p=69036#p69036</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7089&amp;p=69036#p69036"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[6502 asm in notepad ++]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7089&amp;p=69036#p69036"><![CDATA[
You probably have to modify langs.xml in the Notepad++ installation directory and modify the "ext" here to something else:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&lt;Language name=&quot;asm&quot; ext=&quot;asm&quot; commentLine=&quot;;&quot; commentStart=&quot;&quot; commentEnd=&quot;&quot;&gt;</div><br />Then add "asm" as an extension to your own language definition in userDefineLang.xml.<br /><br />Personally I use .s for 6502 sources so this isn't a problem for me.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=80">thefox</a> — Sat Oct 23, 2010 6:02 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
